 Marie de France, the Gawain-poet, and Chaucer demonstrates how the extravagantly imagined worlds of romance invite reflection about the nature of the real. These stories, which have delighted readers for hundreds of years, do so because the impossible fictions of one era prefigure desired realities for later generations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh1 aKnapp, Peggy, eauthor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishz978311060418408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2018z9783110603187oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Pilot 2017z978311066594908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2019z978311065878108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2016-2017z978311060680508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press ebook package 2017z978311063896740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781487514204423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487514204.jpg  a978-3-11-060418-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060680-5  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2016-2017  a978-3-11-063896-7  University of Toronto Press ebook package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-065878-1  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2019b2019  a978-3-11-066594-9  UTP eBook-Package Pilot 2017  aEBA_BACKAL